-- Renault Plans to Sell Electric Cars for Less Than $19,500, Le Figaro Says
-- Tara Patel
-- 2010-07-27T05:41:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/renault-to-sell-electric-cars-for-less-than-eu15-000-le-figaro-reports.html

          
          
             Renault SA  plans to sell its Zoe
electric car starting mid-2012 for less than 15,000 euros
($19,500) ,  Le Figaro  reported, citing an unidentified company
official.  
 The cost of the Zoe is about the same as a diesel-fueled
model of similar size, the newspaper said.  
 The price includes a 5,000-euro credit from the government
and buyers will have to pay 100 euros a month to rent the
battery for the car, the newspaper said.  
 About 150,000 models will be produced annually at the
companyâ€™s plant in Flins, France, Figaro said.  
